Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Lay the @Irish Bacon{130%grams} in a single layer on a lined #baking tray{}.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until golden brown and crispy, ~{10-15%minutes}.
> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

> TIP: You can pan-fry the bacon if you prefer.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @Tomato{2}.

Cut the @Baguette{2%unit(s)} down the middle lengthways.

Pop them into the oven, cut-side up, to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.
> TIP: You can toast your bread in the toaster if you'd like.

Spread the @Cream Cheese{48%grams} over the cut side of the baguette bases.

Top with @Salad Leaves{40%grams} (as much or as little as you like).

Layer the tomato and then the bacon on top of the salad. Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

Sandwich closed with the top of the baguette.

Slice in half widthways and plate up.